children.subject: There was an issue with the class settings that prevented the wait list from being run. I fixed that this afternoon and the wait list has now been processed. It should continue to do so just fine.

Hi!

I am 9th on the wait list (and have been since Phase 1), but have not yet been added to the class. Do you know when the wait list will begin processing? Thanks!!

history.content:
Many of you have been asking the advisers so I confirmed with the faculty that this class will NOT expand past the current enrollment cap of 1296.

Once the adjustment period opens on Monday 8/13, any open seats will be automatically filled from the wait list.(As of 8/9 there are currently 54 open seats.)

If you are NOT in the first 180 positions on the wait list, I strongly recommend that you have a back up plan and consider finding another class to attend. (Remember, the rule of thumb is to expect appx. 10% of enrolled students to drop by the add/drop deadline of Sept 12th.)

If you haven't yet enrolled, and wish to put yourself on the wait list, I am sorry to say you will need to try again in SP19 semester.
